{:title "Wire up remaining phase interceptors (verify, review, release)"
 :description "Complete the phase interceptor migration by wiring up agent invocation in the remaining 3 phases.

We successfully wired plan.clj and implement.clj - now need to apply the same pattern to:
- verify.clj
- review.clj
- release.clj

Pattern established (from plan.clj):
```clojure
(ns ai.miniforge.phase.plan
  (:require [ai.miniforge.phase.registry :as registry]
            [ai.miniforge.agent.interface :as agent]
            [ai.miniforge.agent.planner :as planner]))

(defn- enter-plan [ctx]
  (let [planner-agent (planner/create-planner {})
        task {...}
        result (agent/invoke planner-agent task ctx)]
    (assoc-in ctx [:phase :result] result)))

(defn- leave-plan [ctx]
  (let [metrics (get-in ctx [:phase :result :metrics])]
    (-> ctx
        (assoc-in [:phase :metrics] metrics)
        (update-in [:execution/metrics :tokens] + (:tokens metrics 0)))))
```

For each phase:
1. Import specialized agent (tester for verify, reviewer for review, releaser for release)
2. Update enter-* to create specialized agent and invoke it
3. Update leave-* to extract and merge metrics
4. Build appropriate task context from previous phase outputs

Success criteria:
- All 3 phases wire up agent invocation
- verify uses create-tester
- review uses create-reviewer
- release uses appropriate agent
- Metrics properly tracked
- Pattern matches plan/implement

Reference:
- components/phase/src/ai/miniforge/phase/plan.clj (completed example)
- components/phase/src/ai/miniforge/phase/implement.clj (completed example)
- components/agent/src/ai/miniforge/agent/tester.clj (has create-tester)
- components/agent/src/ai/miniforge/agent/reviewer.clj (has create-reviewer)"

